  "prompt": "Will I get refund after preparation of chart for wait listed ticket?",
  "response": "Yes, if you have a waitlisted ticket and the chart has been prepared without your ticket being confirmed, you are generally entitled to a refund. The specific details can vary based on the policies of the railway or airline you are dealing with, as well as the ticket type and local regulations.\n\nFor railway tickets in India, for example, if your waitlisted ticket remains unconfirmed by the time the final chart is prepared, it is usually automatically canceled, and you will receive a full refund, typically credited back to your account. It's advisable to check the specific refund policies of the service provider you're dealing with to ensure you have the most accurate information.",
